	<h2><a href="http://www.boston.com/sports/blogs/bigshots/2012/01/big_shots_for_january_4_2012.html">Big Shots for January 4, 2012</a></h2>
	<span class="blogText bigText"><div class="bpBody">This week Big Shots dons our lederhosen in the Alps for the Four Hills ski jumping tournament, gets our beers spilled courtside as the NBA returns to action, and wonders if a winter swimmer in Harbin, China ever came up for air.  Check out The Big Picture next week for an in-depth look at the Dakar Rally in progress now in South America.   (<a href="http://www.boston.com/sports/blogs/bigshots/2012/01/big_shots_for_january_4_2012.html"> 32 photos total</a>)</div><div class="bpImageTop"><a name="photo1"></a><a href="http://www.boston.com/sports/blogs/bigshots/2012/01/big_shots_for_january_4_2012.html"><img src="http://cache.boston.com/multimedia/sports/bigshots/010412/bs1.jpg" class="bpImage" style="height:1084px;width:959px" /></a><br/><div class="bpCaption">New York Knicks fan Freddy Klein, who has had Knicks seats for 52 years, waits for the Knicks' NBA basketball game against the Boston Celtics to start at Madison Square Garden on Dec. 25, 2011. (Kathy Willens/AP)<div class="cf"></div></div></div></span>
	<span class="bpMore">
	<p><br />
