<div class="bpBoth"><a name="photo3"></a><img src="http://cache.boston.com/multimedia/sports/bigshots/010412/bs3.jpg" class="bpImage" style="height:748px;width:959px" /><br/><div class="bpCaption"><div class="photoNum"><a href="#photo3">3</a></div>Is it something he ate?  A college football fan grimaces at the 2012 Fiesta Bowl between Stanford and Oklahoma State  in Glendale, Arizona January 2, 2012.  (Rick Scuteri/Reuters) <a href="#photo3">#</a><div class="cf"></div></div></div><br />
<div class="bpBoth"><a name="photo4"></a><img src="http://cache.boston.com/multimedia/sports/bigshots/010412/bs4.jpg" class="bpImage" style="height:849px;width:959px" /><br/><div class="bpCaption"><div class="photoNum"><a href="#photo4">4</a></div>Larry Fitzgerald of the Arizona Cardinals grimaces before the NFL game against the Seattle Seahawks on January 1, 2012 in Glendale, Arizona.  What are they putting in the water in Glendale?  (Christian Petersen/Getty Images) <a href="#photo4">#</a><div class="cf"></div></div></div><br />
